  "title": "Event Ticketing & Marketplace Sales Assistants (6–7 Months)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Contract Duration:</strong> Feb 2026 – Aug 2026<br /><strong>Positions Available:</strong> 1<br /><strong>Work Hours:</strong> Mon–Fri, 8:30am–6:00pm<br /><strong>Work Locations:</strong> Singapore Botanic Gardens | Gardens by the Bay (during show & setup period)<br /><strong>Salary:</strong> $16.00 – $18.00 per hour<br /><strong>Qualification:</strong> Diploma to Degree</p><p><strong>About the Role:</strong></p><p>We are looking for two proactive and customer-focused individuals to join the team as Event Ticketing & Marketplace Sales Assistants. You will play a key role in driving ticket sales, supporting event operations, and ensuring smooth coordination in the lead-up to a major event happening in July 2026.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Generate group ticket sales through outreach, cold calls, and engagement with communities, corporates, and government organisations.</li><li>Serve as the main point of contact for customer enquiries via phone and email.</li><li>Assist with scheduling and coordination of group tours.</li><li>Handle after-sales follow-up and ensure accurate documentation.</li><li>Work with third-party vendors to reconcile accounts and sales information.</li><li>Coordinate with Finance on revenue tracking and reporting.</li><li>Support Marketplace booth sales operations.</li><li>Assist with marketing tasks, including coordination with the appointed PR agency.</li><li>Support roadshows and publicity activities leading up to the July 2026 event.</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as required.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in any discipline</li><li>Good communication and customer service skills</li><li>Comfortable with outreach, cold calling, and handling enquiries</li><li>Organised, detail-oriented, and able to multitask</li><li>Able to start work in <strong>February 2026</strong></li><li>Able to work at event locations when required</li></ul><p><br />EA License No.: 96C4864</p><p>Reg No.: R25128798 HUANG QIMENG</p><p></p>",
